      "description": "## Building UIs Like LEGO\n\nImagine building a house with LEGO:\n1. You start with **individual bricks** (smallest pieces)\n2. Combine bricks into **small structures** (a window, a door)\n3. Combine structures into **rooms** (a bedroom, a kitchen)\n4. Combine rooms into a **complete house**\n\n### We build websites the same way!\n\nThis approach is called **Atomic Design**:\n\n| Level | LEGO Equivalent | Web Example |\n|-------|----------------|-------------|\n| **Atoms** | Single bricks | Button, Icon, Input |\n| **Molecules** | Small structures | Search bar, Card |\n| **Organisms** | Rooms | Navigation, Footer |\n| **Layouts** | Floor plans | Page template |\n| **Pages** | Complete house | Home page |\n\n### Why build this way?\n- Small pieces are **easier to understand**\n- You can **reuse** pieces everywhere\n- Changes in one place **update everywhere**"
    },
