      "file": "src/components/atoms/Button/Button.tsx",
      "line": 1,
      "description": "## What are Atoms?\n\nAtoms are the **smallest, most basic** building blocks. They can't be broken down further.\n\n### Real-world atoms in our app:\n- A **Button** you can click\n- An **Icon** (like ‚ô• or ‚òÖ)\n- A text **Input** box\n- A **Rating** (stars)\n- A **Price** display\n\n### Characteristics of atoms:\n1. **Simple** - Does one thing only\n2. **Reusable** - Used in many places\n3. **Independent** - Works on its own\n\n### Example:\nA button can say \"Book Now\", \"Login\", or \"Add to Cart\". The same Button atom is used everywhere, just with different text and colors!"
