      "line": 1,
      "description": "## Component Props (Options)\n\nProps are the **options** you can pass to a component. Think of them like settings.\n\n### Button has these options:\n\n```typescript\ninterface ButtonProps {\n  size?: 'xs' | 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg' | 'xl';  // How big?\n  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary' | ...;   // What color?\n  buttonStyle?: 'solid' | 'outline' | ...;   // What style?\n  loading?: boolean;                          // Show spinner?\n  disabled?: boolean;                         // Clickable or not?\n  children: ReactNode;                        // The text inside\n}\n```\n\n### The `?` means optional:\nIf you don't provide a value, a default is used.\n\n### Why define props?\n- **TypeScript catches errors** - Can't pass invalid values\n- **Autocomplete** - Editor suggests valid options\n- **Documentation** - Props tell you how to use the component"
