      "line": 1,
      "description": "## The Skeleton Atom\n\nShows a **placeholder** while content is loading.\n\n### What is it?\nYou've seen this on Facebook, YouTube, etc. - gray boxes that pulse while the real content loads. This is called a \"skeleton screen\".\n\n### Why use skeletons?\n- **Better than spinners** - Users see the page structure\n- **Feels faster** - Users feel like something is happening\n- **Professional look** - Modern UX pattern\n\n### Types:\n```tsx\n// For images/cards\n<Skeleton variant=\"block\" width={200} height={150} />\n\n// For text lines\n<Skeleton variant=\"text\" count={3} />\n\n// For profile pictures\n<Skeleton variant=\"circle\" size={50} />\n```\n\n### Where we use it:\nWhen fetching homestays, we show skeleton cards until the real data arrives."
