      "description": "## The SearchBar Molecule\n\nAnother molecule combining atoms.\n\n### What it combines:\n- **Input** atom (the text box)\n- **Icon** atom (magnifying glass)\n- **Button** atom (search button)\n\n### Using the SearchBar:\n```tsx\n<SearchBar \n  placeholder=\"Where do you want to go?\"\n  onSearch={(query) => console.log(query)}\n/>\n```\n\n### The molecule handles:\n- User typing in the box\n- Pressing Enter or clicking Search\n- Calling your function with the search text\n\n### Why make it a molecule?\nYou could use an Input and Button separately, but combining them:\n- Keeps pages cleaner\n- Ensures consistent search UI everywhere\n- Contains the search logic in one place"
