      "file": "src/components/layouts/MainLayout/MainLayout.tsx",
      "line": 1,
      "description": "## What are Layouts?\n\nLayouts are **page templates** that provide consistent structure.\n\n### Think of a newspaper:\n- Every page has the same **header** (newspaper name)\n- Every page has the same **footer** (page number)\n- Only the **content in the middle** changes\n\n### MainLayout provides:\n1. Skip link (for keyboard users)\n2. Navbar at the top\n3. Space for the page content\n4. Footer at the bottom\n5. Mobile navigation (on phones)\n\n### Why layouts matter:\n- **Write once, use everywhere** - Don't repeat navbar code on every page\n- **Consistency** - All pages have the same structure\n- **Easier maintenance** - Update navbar once, it changes everywhere"
