      "description": "## How Layouts Work\n\nThe layout wraps around page content:\n\n```tsx\n<div className=\"min-h-screen flex flex-col\">\n  {/* Always at top */}\n  <Navbar />\n  \n  {/* Page content goes here */}\n  <main className=\"flex-grow\">\n    {children}  {/* or <Outlet /> for React Router */}\n  </main>\n  \n  {/* Always at bottom */}\n  <Footer />\n  \n  {/* Mobile only */}\n  <MobileNav />\n</div>\n```\n\n### The `children` prop:\nWhatever you put between the layout tags becomes `children`.\n\n```tsx\n<MainLayout>\n  <HomePage />  {/* This becomes 'children' */}\n</MainLayout>\n```\n\n### React Router uses `<Outlet />`:\nWith routing, `<Outlet />` is where child routes render."
